abstract: >-
  inspect-evidence-sufficiency turns an agent eval trace into an
  Evidence-Sufficiency-Card: a reviewer-facing report of which evidence fields
  are present, partial, or missing before an eval result is used as release
  evidence, reproducible byte-for-byte given fixed inputs and a pinned timestamp. It reads Inspect-style logs, ControlArena trajectory
  exports, and generic agent trace JSON/JSONL, and scores twelve evidence fields
  (eval objective and release decision, task/dataset scope, model/provider
  binding, prompt/scaffold/policy identity, tools and permissions, raw
  messages/events/tool calls, scorer and monitor identity, retries/errors,
  transcript and replay handle, counterfactual replay, leakage and
  reward-hacking checks, and an explicit not-sufficient-for statement) into a
  conservative verdict. The artifact is evidence-bound: it reports which
  evidence a trace contains, never model quality, benchmark validity, safety, or
  audit/compliance sufficiency.
